<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--BirthdayWhale     11-27 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Birthday Whale,0168</SECOND>
<HEAD>Baby Shamu Celebrates First Birthday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN ANTONIO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The four-day party for Baby Shamu
ended with the killer whale extinguishing a candle on her birthday
cake with a playful squirt.
   ``We've had a pretty exciting weekend here with her,'' said Thad
Lacinak, director of animal training for Sea World of Texas.
``She's quite a ham.''
   The 1,100-pound whale, who turned 1 Sunday, is the first
Texas-born killer whale and the fifth born in the United States.
The others were born at the Sea Worlds in California or Florida.
   Baby Shamu has been performing some routines with her mother,
Lacinak said. But this was the first time the baby whale held
center stage alone.
   She does head stands, fast swims, flipper waves and bow jumps
out of the water, he said.
   Its mother, Namu, is taking her child's newfound independence
quite well, Lacinak said.
   ``Just like people it depends on the personality of the
parent,'' he said.
</TEXT>
