<HEAD>Hawaiian Takes Japanese Sumo Title</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FUKUOKA, Japan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 488 lb. Hawaiian on Sunday won the
Kyushu Grand Sumo Tournament.
   Salevaa Fuauli Atisanoe, known as Konishiki, thrust Sekiwake
Kotogaume out of the ring to clinch the tournament championship.
The 25-year-old wrestler received a message from President Bush,
telling him he gave all Americans something to boast about.
   The only other foreign wrestler ever to win a major tournament
in the traditional Japanese sport, fellow Hawaiian Jesse Kuhaulua,
told Japan's Kyodo News Service, ``I am more joyful than when I won
the championship'' in 1972.
   Atisanoe started in football, starring at fullback for a
Honolulu prep school team.
