I said, `We're not going to do that.''' _ Edwin J. Gray, former
chairman of the Federal Home Loan Bank Board, insisting that five
U.S. senators improperly pressured him as a favor to Charles H.
Keating Jr., owner of the now collapsed Lincoln Savings and Loan
Association.
