<FIRST>r a PM-BabyKilled     11-27 0189</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Baby Killed,0196</SECOND>
<HEAD>Infant Killed By Pipe Aimed At Man Who Grabbed Him</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 4-month-old boy caught in a fight between two
men, one who was raising the child and the other who said he was
the infant's natural father, died after being struck by a section
of pipe, police said.
   Daniel Jorgenson was killed Saturday after a man barged into an
apartment, claiming to be the infant's father, said police Sgt.
Mary Wrensen.
   ``They were fighting and the baby was in the middle,'' the boy's
mother, Diane Jorgenson, told reporters.
   Wrensen said 25-year-old Juan Nogueras forced his way into the
apartment where the child lived with his mother and Alfredo Acosta,
39.
   Nogueras grabbed the boy and then ran outside with the child.
   Acosta chased him, wielding a 3-foot-long pipe, Wrensen said.
   ``Acosta struck Nogueras in the head and also struck the baby,
killing the baby,'' Wrensen said.
   Nogueras was charged with burglary but any other charges in the
case will be considered by the Brooklyn district attorney's office,
she said.
   It was not clear who was the child's father, the officer said.
