<HEAD>British Robber Frozen in His Tracks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HELSINKI, Finland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 38-year-old British bank robber
surrendered after his getaway car froze to a standstill, newspapers
reported Monday.
   The man, who was not identified, confessed to three bank
robberies in Finland since August and two in Sweden, the media
reported.
   Police found the abandoned British-registered car on the road
outside Helsinki, where temperatures have fallen to 3 degrees below
