<SECOND>AM-Child Slain,0231</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Men Charged in Slaying of 3-Year-Old</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOBILE, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunfight between relatives of two women
feuding over boyfriends claimed a young victim _ a 3-year-old boy
in a parked car whose mother tried to shield him from the gunfire.
   Two men were charged Monday with murder, police spokesman Tom
Jennings said.
   Leonard Ray Williams Jr. was fatally wounded Sunday when the two
groups fought on a street in a north Mobile neighborhood, Jennings
said.
   The slain boy's mother, Sylvia Rivers, 28, had stopped her car
at a relative's home where they planned to have lunch. When she
heard the gunfire, she reached for the boy, who was seated in the
front of the car, but a bullet shattered the windshield and killed
him, Jennings said.
   Mrs. Rivers, who was not involved in the feuding, was treated
for shock at a hospital.
   The slaying followed a bar fight Saturday night between the two
women; the feud had been simmering for three weeks, police said.
   Jerry Harrison, 40, was charged with murder Sunday when he came
to the police station to ask about the incident, Jennings said.
Witnesses had identified Harrison as one of three men in a pickup
truck involved in the shooting.
   Michael Anthony Simmons, 26, also was charged with murder when
he surrendered to police Monday morning.
