<HEAD>It's A Girl for Dan Aykroyd and Donna Dixon</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   It's a girl for actor Dan Aykroyd and his
actress-wife Donna Dixon.
   Danielle Alexandra weighed 8 pounds, 13 ounces when she took her
first breath of air on Nov. 18 at 12:05 p.m., said Susan Patricola,
publicist for the couple.
   The couple wanted to get the baby out of St. John's Hospital and
Health Center and home for Thanksgiving before a birth announcement
was made, Patricola said Monday.
   ``They're thrilled with their new arrival. She's healthy and
beautiful and they're looking forward to parenthood,'' Patricola
said.
   Aykroyd, who rose from the original cast of the ``Saturday Night
Live'' television show to motion pictures with his pal and ex-Blues
Brothers cohort John Belushi, stars in the Dec. 13 release of the
movie ``Driving Miss Daisy.''
   Miss Dixon was on the old ``Bosom Buddies'' TV series.
</TEXT>
