<HEAD>Parents Kill Themselves in Front of Children</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CRYSTAL RIVER, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A couple who had been arguing about
their upcoming divorce shot and killed themselves in front of three
of their children, authorities said.
   The children told Citrus County sheriff's deputies that their
mother picked up a small-caliber pistol Sunday afternoon and shot
herself once in the head. Her husband then picked up the gun an
shot himself in the head.
   Arcanio Joseph Rivera, 42, and Maria A. Rivera, 33, were dead on
arrival at Citrus Memorial Hospital, deputies said.
   They had separated, said sheriff's Sgt. Wayne Burns. The man
lived at the mobile home where the shooting occurred. Burns did not
know where the woman lived.
   The couple's four children, whose ages ranged from 10 to 15,
also lived in the mobile home. Three sons saw the shootings, Burns
said. Their sister was visiting a friend.
