<HEAD>Edward Kennedy to Speak Where Brother Addressed West Berliners</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sen. Edward M. Kennedy will visit the scene
of one of his brother's most electric moments Tuesday and speak at
the site where President John F. Kennedy declared, in German: ``I
am a Berliner.''
   The Massachussetts Democrats is to lay a wreath in the late
president's memory at Schoeneberg City Hall in West Berlin, where
John F. Kennedy spoke to 400,000 people on June 26, 1963.
   ``All free men, wherever they may live, are citizens of
Berlin,'' he told to the cheering crowd. ``And therefore, as a free
man, I take pride in the words, `Ich bin ein Berliner.'''
