<HEAD>American Buys Lenin Death Mask</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The first death mask of Vladimir Ilyich Lenin,
founder of the Soviet Union, sold Monday to an unidentified
American for $10,200, Phillips auction house said.
   The mask apparently was cast by sculptor Sergei Merkurov on Jan.
21, 1934, the night Lenin died at age 53 after suffering two
strokes.
   It was part of a sale of 20th-century Russian art that was
recently allowed out of the Soviet Union.
   A porcelain bust of Lenin's successor, Joseph Stalin, made in
Leningrad in 1947, did not sell.
