<TEXT>
   The attorney general Monday reinstated a
first-degree murder charge against a man in the 1976 car-bomb
assassination of investigative reporter Don Bolles, saying he had
turned up new evidence.
   James Albert Robison, who was charged in a complaint filed in
Maricopa County Superior Court, who is serving a prison term for an
unrelated assault.
   Attorney General Bob Corbin said the investigation into the
Arizona Republic reporter's slaying would continue, but would not
