<HEAD>For Release Saturday, Dec. 9</HEAD>
<HEAD>Today In History</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Today is Saturday, December 9, the 343rd day of 1989. There are
22 days left in the year.
   Today's highlight in history:
   On December 9, 1907, Christmas seals went on sale for the first
time, in the Wilmington, Del., post office. The proceeds went to
fight tuberculosis.
   On this date:
   In 1608, English poet John Milton was born in London.
   In 1854, Alfred, Lord Tennyson's famous poem, ``The Charge of
the Light Brigade,'' was published in England.
   In 1884, Levant M. Richardson of Chicago received a patent for
the ball-bearing roller skate.
   In 1940, British troops opened their first major offensive in
North Africa during World War II.
   In 1941, China declared war on Japan, Germany and Italy.
   In 1958, Robert H.W. Welch Jr. and eleven other men met in
Indianapolis to form the anti-Communist John Birch Society.
   In 1965, Nikolai V. Podgorny replaced Anastas I. Mikoyan as
president of the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet.
   In 1975, President Ford signed a $2.3 billion seasonal
loan-authorization that officials of New York City and State said
would prevent a city default.
   In 1982, Leon Jaworski, the Watergate special prosecutor who
played a key role in forcing the resignation of President Nixon in
1974, died at his Wimberly, Texas, ranch at age 77.
   Ten years ago: Archbishop Fulton J. Sheen, the religious
broadcaster, died in New York City at the age of 84.
   Five years ago: The five-day-old hijacking of a Kuwaiti jetliner
that claimed the lives of two Americans ended as Iranian security
men seized control of the plane, which was parked at Tehran airport.
   One year ago: In the wake of the Armenian earthquake that
claimed tens of thousands of lives, countries around the world
began sending emergency supplies and offering pledges of relief
funds.
   Today's Birthdays: Actor Douglas Fairbanks Jr. is 80. Former
House Speaker Thomas ``Tip'' O'Neill is 77. Actor Kirk Douglas is
73. Comedian Redd Foxx is 67. Actress Dina Merrill is 64. Actor
Dick Van Patten is 61. Actor Beau Bridges is 48. Former football
player Dick Butkus is 47. Singer Joan Armatrading is 39. Actor John
Malkovich is 36. Singer Donny Osmond is 32.
   Thought for Today: ``I would rather have men ask why I have no
statue than why I have one.'' _ Marcus Porcius Cato, Roman
statesman and historian (234 B.C.-149 B.C.).
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Advance for Use Saturday, December 9</NOTE>
