<HEAD>Premiere Magazine Publisher Named to Group Sales Post</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The publisher of Premiere Magazine, Peter W.
Eldredge, was named Monday to head a sales unit responsible for
getting large advertisers to buy space in multiple titles within
News Corp. Ltd.'s Murdoch Magazines group.
   In the newly created post of vice president-group sales,
Eldredge will also help combine multi-media packages for
advertisers matching the magazines with News Corp.'s other
divisions, which include Fox Inc.'s television network.
   Replacing Eldredge as publisher of Premiere will be Marian L.
Schwindeman, currently the magazine's associate publisher.
   Murdoch Magazines President John B. Evans said in announcing the
appointments that the magazine group has gone through a period of
very rapid growth, including last year's purchase of TV Guide and
Seventeen magazines.
   Total average circulation for the group is more than 25 million
per issue. Other magazines in the group include Automobile,
Mirabella, New Woman, New York Magazine, Soap Opera Digest, Soap
Opera Weekly and Star.
   Eldredge, 45, was publisher of Star for two years before being
appointed publisher of Premiere in June 1987. He joined Murdoch
Magazines in 1984 after eight years at Money Magazine, a Time
Warner Inc. publication.
   Ms. Schwindeman, 37, joined Premiere in November 1986 after
working for six years at The Village Voice, a weekly newspaper in
New York.
